#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "38. Sannidhikārakasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 38: the training rule on storing"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.38.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.338"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa812"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: belaṭṭhasīso → bellaṭṭhisīso (bj) | belaṭṭhisīso (si) | veḷaṭṭhasīso (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa upajjhāyo āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso araññe viharati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Belaṭṭhasīsa, Venerable Ānanda’s preceptor, was staying in the wilderness."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "So piṇḍāya caritvā sukkhakuraṃ ārāmaṃ haritvā sukkhāpetvā nikkhipati."
msgstr "After walking for alms, he brought plain boiled rice back to the monastery, where he dried and stored it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Yadā āhārena attho hoti, tadā udakena temetvā temetvā bhuñjati, cirena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisati."
msgstr "Whenever he got hungry, he moistened it and ate it. As a consequence, he only re-entered the village for alms after a long time."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ belaṭṭhasīsaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, cirena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why do you only re-enter the village for alms after such a long time?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told them."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“But do you eat food that you’ve stored?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa813"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Belaṭṭhasīsa eat food that he has stored?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Belaṭṭhasīsa, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjissasi."
msgstr "Belaṭṭhasīsa, how can you eat food that you have stored?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.18a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.87"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa814"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.339"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats staple or non-staple food that he has stored, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "(<em>38</em>:<strong>87</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.38.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.38.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa815"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa816"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Sannidhikārakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "That he has stored:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "ajja paṭiggahitaṃ aparajju khāditaṃ hoti."
msgstr "received today and eaten on the following day."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa817"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the five staple foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa818"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple food:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa819"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives staple or non-staple food with the intention of eating it, he commits and offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.38.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa820"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Sannidhikārake sannidhikārakasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has been stored, and he perceives that it has been stored, and he eats the staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Sannidhikārake vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has been stored, but he is unsure if it has, and he eats the staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Sannidhikārake asannidhikārakasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it has been stored, but he perceives that it has not been stored, and he eats the staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa821"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Asannidhikārake sannidhikārakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it has not been stored, but he perceives that it has been stored, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Asannidhikārake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it has not been stored, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Asannidhikārake asannidhikārakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it has not been stored, and he perceives that it has not been stored, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.38.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa822"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "yāvakālikaṃ yāvakāle nidahitvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he stores and eats it during the right time;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.340"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "yāmakālikaṃ yāme nidahitvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he stores and eats post-midday tonics during the remainder of the day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "sattāhakālikaṃ sattāhaṃ nidahitvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he stores and eats seven-day tonics during the seven-day period;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he uses lifetime tonics when there is a reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa823"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc38:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "Sannidhikārakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on storing, is finished."

